        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "PostgREST JWT access token",
        "setup": "Obtain a JWT for a database role that PostgREST recognizes in the token's `role` claim. In the simplest setup, configure your PostgREST instance with a JWT secret or public key, then mint/sign a JWT that includes the desired role and send it as `Authorization: Bearer <jwt>`. See the [Authentication](https://docs.postgrest.org/en/v14/references/auth.html) docs for role-based request authentication and the [JWT Generation](https://docs.postgrest.org/en/v14/references/auth.html#jwt-generation) section for token setup.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      },
      "pgrst_db_auth": {
        "type": "basic",
        "label": "PostgREST database connection credentials",
        "setup": "Create or choose a PostgreSQL role/password pair for the PostgREST server's database connection, then place it in the server configuration as the `db-uri` connection string. The docs describe `db-uri` as the way to provide the database connection details; the easiest path is usually to keep the URI in the config file and run PostgREST with that file. See the [Configuration](https://docs.postgrest.org/en/v14/references/configuration.html) docs for `db-uri` and config-file usage.",
        "acquisition": "manual"
      }
